<br>
When doing complex of FUBAR'd splits, sometimes you have a tiny window of opportunity to get it right. I, too, generally pull with HoS, or tag and DA, or whatever. I want to be able to fade and reaggro the /instant/ it seems advantageous to do so. Not 3 seconds later. <br>
<br>
Boastful bellow is really pretty cheap. I'd just buy it before you cross far beyond 100 AAs (after Fade, instrument mastery, etc ... the essentials). You'll find uses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pickkpockket999>Pickk Pockket999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#330000>(3/25/04 4:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19197.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: if you pull...</span><hr size=1> One super secret trick to bellow pulling:<br>
<br>
Lets pretend there is an unlullable unmezzable named you want to single pull to your group but there is an add behind him that you can't get LoS on.<br>
<br>
You sing harmony of sound on the named and start singing mez on him even though he is unmezzable. Hopefully that add aggroed and partway through your mez song he is finally targetable. You click on the add, bellow to change targets mid mez cast and bam you just mezzed the add, have the named inc debuffed and didn't require any large amount of room to accomplish this in.<br>
<br>
I use this trick all the time in GoD where repops are fast and I don't have lots of room to mez adds on inc. Don't discount AA Bellow it is an amazing tool (it rocks in PvP too). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zebulas>Zebulas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#330000>(3/25/04 5:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19197.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: if you pull...</span><hr size=1> great trick pickk!  Thanks for sharing.<br>
